reviews.review_text: Another perspective Most of us have this run as clean boards. This here is a great inital taper attempt and evidence of modern day technical assistance thus giving us an above average AUD with the sound and flavor of good ole Dead,can you say PIG!PEACE 2006'

Its worth a download If you are not sure wether get this one, just download I Know You Rider, and choose, if you like hearing the audience going crazy, or if you prefer sterile soundboards (which you wonÃÂ´t get anyways).I have to admit, that this recording is not one of the best IÃÂ´ve heard, but sometimes IÃÂ´m (and I bet some of you too) in the mood to listen to a concert in minor quality with the people`s reactions , just to get an image of how it has been back then.

Happier than a Pig in Mud Heartfelt gratitude to Clinton Vadnais & friends and Archive.org for this fabulous gift this morning.

I was fiddling around with my Pandora thumbs to improve their customized algorithm for me, and up popped "Good Lovin'" from the album 3 for the vault. I was blown away, overjoyed, delighted, you name it.  So I looked for the show in the archives, and sure enough 3 of the 4 can't be heard due to commercial considerations.  But this one is there, and what a diamond in the not so rough...

My love affair with all things PigPen intensifies with the onset of spring. If you feel this way too, just stop what you are doing, turn on the show, and get back to your business.

A very basic tech tip:  if you got cheap laptop speakers like me, set them at about 85% volume and listen from across the room.

As for the audience applause cadence issue?
